    <p><em>The Maldives</em> is a paradise destination known for its crystal clear waters, white sand beaches, and incredible marine biodiversity. They are located in the <em>Indian Ocean,</em> southwest of <em>Sri Lanka</em> and <em>India,</em> and consist of approximately 1,200 islands</p>
    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Bolifushi.jpg/1200px-Bolifushi.jpg" width="190" >
    
    
    
    
</html>     <h2>List of activities to do in the Maldives</h2>
<ol>
    <li>Diving and snorkeling: The clear waters and colorful coral reefs make the Maldives a paradise for diving and snorkeling.                
    
   <li>Water sports: You can practice kayaking, paddleboarding, surfing and kitesurfing.
    
   <li>Boat excursions: You can take cruises to see dolphins or spectacular sunsets, as well as tours to other islands.</ol>

 <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Alyosha_is_certified.jpg/640px-Alyosha_is_certified.jpg" width="159">
 <h2>Graphic description</h2>
 
<p>Imagine a <strong>tropical</strong> paradise with crystal-clear turquoise waters reflecting the clear blue sky. On the horizon, small islands covered in green vegetation emerge from the ocean, surrounded by white sand beaches. The overwater bungalows are raised on wooden piers, connected by walkways that wind through the shallow waters. Beneath the surface, you see colorful coral reefs teeming with marine life.</p>


<h2>Accommodation</h2>
<ul>
<li>Overwater Resorts: The Maldives is famous for its overwater bungalows or villas, which offer an incredible level of luxury and privacy. They are designed to blend in with the natural surroundings and many have private pools.
</ul>

<img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0c/Adaaran_Club_Rannalhi.jpg/220px-Adaaran_Club_Rannalhi.jpg" width="237">


<h2>Gastronomy</h2>

<strong>Maldivian cuisine</strong> is mainly based on fish, especially tuna, and coconut. Some traditional dishes are "garudhiya" (fish soup) and "mas huni" (mixture of shredded tuna with coconut and onion). There is also influence from Indian and Asian cuisine.

<img src='https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/72/Seafood_dish.jpg/640px-Seafood_dish.jpg'width="190">
